     trips:"Aswan Tourist Trips",   
    archaeological_tours: "Archaeological tours",
    archaeological_sub: "Introducing visitors to Egypt’s ancient and rich history.",
    archaeological_text: "Archaeological trips reveal the greatness of ancient Egyptian civilization. In Aswan, these archaeological tours vary to include a range of unique landmarks spanning multiple historical periods. Among the most notable of these trips is a visit to the Temple of Philae, considered one of the most beautiful ancient Egyptian temples dedicated to the worship of the goddess Isis. It is reached by Nile boats on a journey that combines enjoyment with history. The tours also include a visit to the Unfinished Obelisk, which demonstrates the methods used by the ancient Egyptians to carve obelisks from granite, as well as a visit to the Tombs of the Nobles on the west bank of the Nile. These tombs are distinguished by their carvings that depict scenes of daily life and religious rituals in ancient Egypt. In addition, trips are organized to the Temple of Abu Simbel south of Aswan. These archaeological trips help introduce visitors to Aswan’s rich history and making Aswan a comprehensive destination for archaeological and tourist trips throughout the year.",
    nile_tours: "Nile tours",
    nile_sub: "Visitors can enjoy the tranquility and natural beauty of the Nile.",
    nile_text: "Sailing on a traditional felucca on the Nile offers a calm and enjoyable experience, allowing visitors to watch the sunrise and sunset from the heart of the river as the light reflects beautifully on the water and surrounding mountains. It is also ideal for taking memorable photos and relaxing away from the city’s bustle. Nile tours around the islands include visiting Philae Island and the famous Temple of Isis, as well as exploring Elephantine Island, which features historical ruins and small museums. Travelers can also pass by smaller islands to enjoy the natural scenery and observe migratory birds. For a more comprehensive experience, many tourists opt for Nile cruises—luxurious floating hotels offering multi-day trips, typically 3–4 nights or even a week, between Luxor and Aswan. These cruises include full-board meals, evening entertainment programs, and organized sightseeing tours to major temples and archaeological sites such as the Temple of Philae, Kom Ombo, Edfu, and the High Dam, combining luxury, comfort, and cultural exploration in one journey.",
    cultural_tours: "Cultural and Heritage Tours",
    cultural_sub: "Aswan combines stunning natural beauty with cultural heritage.",
    cultural_text: "Visitors are keen to explore traditional Nubian villages, such as West Sohail, to learn about the customs and daily life of the Nubian people, including traditional clothing, local cuisine, music, and folk dances. Visiting the Nubia Museum and the Aswan Museum is considered one of the most prominent cultural stops, as these museums display thousands of artifacts documenting the history and civilization of Nubia from prehistoric times to the modern era. The museums also provide information about the construction of the High Dam and its impact on the Nubian community, offering a unique educational experience for visitors of all ages. These trips aim to provide a comprehensive experience that combines cultural knowledge with social interaction, leaving tourists with a deep impression of Aswan’s rich heritage and the ancient civilization of its people. Over time, such trips have become an essential part of tourism programs in Aswan, giving visitors the opportunity to learn and enjoy at the same time.",
    market_tours: "Tourist market",
    market_sub: "It includes many bazaars and shops.",
    market_text: "The tourist market in Aswan is considered one of the most important stops on tourist trips within the city, as it brings together folk heritage, daily life, and a tourist atmosphere in one place. The market is located near the Nile Corniche and the railway station, making it easily accessible from hotels and tourist boats. Visitors include the market in their tour programs to learn about the local culture and purchase souvenirs that reflect the spirit of Aswan and Nubia. Trips to the tourist market vary between morning and evening tours. The market includes a large number of shops selling Nubian handicrafts such as wooden statues, replica Pharaonic artifacts, copper, silver, and leather products, in addition to colorful fabrics and traditional Nubian clothing. The market is also famous for selling oriental perfumes, spices, and natural herbs used by the people of Upper Egypt in traditional medicine.",
    desert_tours: "Desert tours",
    desert_sub: "Enchanting natural scenery including sand dunes, rocky mountains, small oases, and unique desert flora.",
    desert_text: "These trips usually begin with rides in four-wheel-drive vehicles on exciting safari tours, allowing visitors to explore the desert terrain, capture panoramic photos of the landscapes, or stop at ancient archaeological sites such as rock inscriptions and small temples scattered across certain areas. In addition, desert trips often include camel rides across the sand dunes, a popular activity among tourists that offers an authentic adventure and insight into traditional desert travel. Many trips also involve overnight stays in desert camps, where visitors can enjoy the clear, star-filled sky and listen to local stories and legends about the desert, the Nile, and the surrounding regions. These trips combine adventure and relaxation, offering a chance to connect with nature and discover the peaceful and scenic side of Aswan beyond the Nile and the city.",
    relax_tours: "Relaxation and tranquility tours",
    relax_sub: "A unique experience for those seeking comfort and relaxation amidst breathtaking nature.",
    relax_text: "One of the main activities in leisure trips is strolling along the Nile Corniche, where visitors can enjoy walking among trees and fountains while admiring the scenic views of the river and the small islands scattered across it. This area offers peaceful spots for contemplation or photography, with enchanting views of the sunrise and sunset. Ferial Park and the surrounding green areas are also ideal places for relaxation and rest. Visitors can sit in the shade, read, or simply enjoy the tranquility and fresh air, away from the city’s noise. These trips combine the beauty of nature with the spirit of the river, making Aswan a perfect destination for those seeking leisure and serenity far from the hustle and bustle of daily life.",
    medical_tours: "Medical tours",
    medical_sub: "This is based on its dry, sunny climate and unique natural characteristics.",
    medical_text: "Aswan is renowned as a global wellness destination, offering a variety of therapeutic treatments such as hot sand therapy for rheumatism, sulfur baths, mud therapy, and hot stone massages, along with the benefits of ultraviolet sunlight. The city hosts fully equipped health resorts and specialized centers, including the Magdi Yacoub Heart Center, making it ideal for treating bone and respiratory ailments. Medical tourism in Aswan combines traditional and modern therapies. Visitors can experience sand therapy by being buried in hot sand to relieve rheumatism and joint problems, a practice dating back to the Pharaonic era, while taking necessary sun precautions. The region’s dry, sunny climate with low humidity and strong UV rays is particularly beneficial for chest diseases and asthma. These offerings make Aswan a comprehensive destination for both therapeutic care and restorative leisure."
               
